          <text><![CDATA[<p>Employee Paycheck Protection Act - Requires a labor organization, before imposing, collecting, or increasing member or other covered employee dues or fees, to provide all employees covered by a collective bargaining agreement with written notice explaining how it calculated the share of such dues or fees related to non-political costs of collective bargaining.</p> <p>Prohibits a labor organization from collecting dues or fees from non-union employees without their consent.</p>]]></text>
